<TITLE> Students set fire to bus in Dhaka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 13 (bdnews24.com)  Students at Titumir College in the capital set fire to a bus and damaged a number of vehicles following altercation with bus workers on Tuesday. Gulshan zone assistant police commissioner Nurul Alam told bdnews24.com the clash occurred at midday as students picked up a brawl with bus workers of Bengal Paribahan over fare. Traffic came to a halt for about an hour and returned to normal track after 1pm. Students claimed the bus workers had pushed them down from the running bus while the workers claimed the students did not pay any fare. Following the noisy brawl two groups of students smashed a number of vehicles and set ablaze a bus, Alam said. There was no serious damage to the bus as the fire was immediately doused, the police official said. Police reached the spot instantly and brought the situation under control in consultation with the students, he added. bdnews2
